cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with 3D human pose estimation in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new solution that involves developing effective techniques to utilize global information across all frames in a video for high-accuracy bone length prediction.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel joint shift loss to bridge the training of the bone length and bone direction prediction networks, which involves developing a new loss function.
4. cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper deals with 3D human pose estimation, which is a common problem in computer graphics.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with 3D human pose estimation in videos, which is a common problem in multimedia applications.
